<subSubSection id="65A7652EC0734B11FF01488DFE7B3201" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0734B11FF01488DFE7B3201" blockId="18.[192,1440,1495,1558]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0734B11FF01488DFE8B31E5" bold="true" box="[192,316,1496,1522]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The round testaceous marking on the basal ½ of the elytral disc will distinguish the members of this species from congeners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65A7652EC0734B11FF014B70FAEA3390" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0734B11FF014B70FC633319" blockId="18.[191,1440,1573,1807]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0734B11FF014B70FEDC3228" bold="true" box="[192,363,1573,1599]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Redescription.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0734B11FEB04B73FE2B3257" box="[369,412,1574,1600]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Size</emphasis>
. Length 11.0 mm; width 
<quantity id="EA459B40C0734B11FD744B73FCBA3257" box="[693,781,1574,1600]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0734B11FCD64B73FCE53228" box="[791,850,1574,1599]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation id="B5862A20C0734B11FC5E4B70FC5A3257" box="[927,1005,1573,1600]" captionStart="Figures 82–85" captionStartId="61.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-38@61.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Figures 82–85. Habitus of Axina species. 82) Axina adelosa. 83) A. bella. 84) A. bifasciata. 85) A. macilenta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565013/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0734B11FC374B70FB843228" box="[1014,1075,1573,1599]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Color</emphasis>
. Forebody, pterothorax, and legs dark castaneous; antenna testaceous; elytra bicolorous, disc mostly castaneous, large round testaceous marking in elytral basal ½, apical 1/3 testaceous; abdomen flavotestaceous. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0734B11FCAB4B3FFC123293" box="[874,933,1642,1668]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons about as wide as length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 55/15. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0734B11FD074BD8FCA432B0" box="[710,787,1677,1703]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, narrowly concave at middle; PW/PL 120/165; elytra with asetiferous punctures concentrated in basal half near sutural margin, interstitial spaces very wide; EL/EW 480/85. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0734B11FD294B87FCE632FB" box="[744,849,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Aedeagus, phallobasic lobes very short, contiguous; edge of phallic plates serrate; phallobasic apodeme slightly lengthened.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0734B11FF014A4AFED4334C" blockId="18.[191,1440,1823,1883]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0734B11FF014A4AFE81332E" bold="true" box="[192,310,1823,1849]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Variation.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0734B11FEFA4A4AFED1332E" box="[315,358,1823,1849]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Size</emphasis>
. Length 10.0–13.0 mm; width 
<quantity id="EA459B40C0734B11FD774A4AFC89332D" box="[694,830,1823,1850]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.85" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.2">2.2–3.5 mm</quantity>
. Other than body size, the available specimens are quite homogeneous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0734B11FF014A39FAEA3390" blockId="18.[192,1373,1900,1927]" box="[192,1373,1900,1927]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0734B11FF014A39FECF3391" bold="true" box="[192,376,1900,1926]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Natural history.</emphasis>
Specimens were collected in 
<collectingCountry id="55AA7635C0734B11FD7F4A39FD483391" box="[702,767,1900,1926]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Brazil</collectingCountry>
during June, November, and December, one at 
<specimenCount id="3BBBFD2CC0734B11FAD04A39FAEA3390" box="[1297,1373,1900,1927]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" type="generic">
<quantity id="EA459B40C0734B11FAD04A39FAEE3390" box="[1297,1369,1900,1927]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" unit="m" value="960.0">960 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
